Step 1: Install MongoDB on Windows

1.1 Download MongoDB

Visit: https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community

Choose version: MongoDB Community Server

Choose platform: Windows

Package: MSI

Click Download


1.2 Install MongoDB

Run the .msi file

Choose Complete setup

Make sure the “Install MongoDB as a Service” option is checked

Click Next and complete the installation


1.3 Verify Installation

Open Command Prompt

Type:

mongo

If installed correctly, you'll enter the MongoDB shell. If not, ensure MongoDB’s bin directory is added to your system’s PATH.



---

Step 2: Install MongoDB Compass (Optional GUI Tool)

Download from: https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/compass

Install and use it to visually interact with databases and collections.



---

Step 3: Start MongoDB Server

MongoDB should run as a service automatically. If not:

net start MongoDB

To run manually:

"C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\<version>\bin\mongod.exe"
